obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (9073)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9073&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Press Council Act, 1978.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (9074)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9074&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Chairman" means the Chairman of the Council;`
  line
  line `(b) "Council" means the Press Council of India established under section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) "member" means a member of the Council and includes its Chairman;`
  line
  line `(d) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) the expressions "editor" and "newspaper" have the meanings respectively assigned to them in`
  line `the Press and Registration of Books Act, 1867 (25 of 1867), and the expression "working journalist"`
  line `has the meaning assigned to it in the Working Journalists and other Newspaper Employees`
  line `(Conditions of Service) and Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1955 (45 of 1955).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (9075)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Rule of construction respecting enactments not extending to the State of Jammu and Kashmir or Sikkim.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9075&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Any reference in this Act to a law which is not in force in ^*the State of ^1`
  line ***
  line `Sikkim shall, in relation to that State, be construed as a reference to the corresponding law, if any, in force`
  line `in that State.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh`
  line
  line `Section 3.--Omit "Jammu and Kashmir or".`
  line
  line `[Vide Jammu and Kashmir Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, Notification No.`
  line `S.O. 1123(E), dated (18-3-2020) and vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "Jammu and Kashmir or" omitted by omitted by the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central`
  line `Laws) Order, 2020, vide notification No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020).`
  line
  line `*. Now applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh by the Notification of`
  line `Government of India, M/o Home Affairs vide No. S.O. 3912 (E), dated 30th October, 2019 (w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (9076)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Incorporation of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9076&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central Government may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint, there shall be established a Council by the name of the`
  line `Press Council of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The said Council shall be a body corporate having perptual succession and a common seal and`
  line `shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (9077)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Composition of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1 . Subs. by Act 36 of 1994, s. 2, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 3-6-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9077&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall consist of a Chairman and twenty-eight other`
  line members.
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman shall be a person nominated by a Committee consisting of the Chairman of the`
  line `Council of States (Rajya Sabha), the Speaker of the House of the People (Lok Sabha) and a person elected`
  line `by the members of the Council under sub-section (6) and the nomination so made shall take effect from`
  line `the date on which it is notified by the Central Government in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(3) Of the other members--`
  line
  line `(a) thirteen shall be nominated in accordance with such procedure as may be prescribed from`
  line `among the working journalists, of whom six shall be editors of newspapers and the remaining seven`
  line `shall be working journalists other than editors; so, however, that the number of such editors and`
  line `working journalists other than editors in relation newspapers published in Indian languages shall be`
  line `not less than three and four respectively;`
  line
  line `(b) six shall be nominated in accordance with such procedure as may be prescribed from among`
  line `persons who own or carry on the business of management of newspapers, so, however, that there shall`
  line `be two representatives from each of the categories of big newspapers, medium newspapers and small`
  line newspapers;
  line
  line `(c) one shall nominated in accordance with such procedure as may be prescribed from among`
  line `persons who manage news agencies;`
  line
  line `(d) three shall be persons having special knowledge or practical experience in respect of`
  line `education and science, law, and literature and culture of whom respectively one shall be nominated by`
  line `the University Grants Commission, one by the Bar Council of India and one by the Sahitya Academy;`
  line
  line `(e) five shall be members of Parliament of whom three shall be nominated by the Speaker from`
  line `among the members of the House of the People (Lok Sabha) and two shall be nominated by the`
  line `Chairman of the Council of States (Rajya Sabha) from among its members:`
  line
  line `Provided that no working journalist who owns, or carries on the business of management of, any`
  line `newspaper shall eligible for nomination under clause (a):`
  line
  line `Provided further that the nominations under clause (a) and clause (b) shall be so made that among`
  line `the persons nominated there is not more than one person interested in any newspaper or group of`
  line `newspapers under the same control of management.`
  line
  line `^1[Explanation.--For the purposes of clause (b), a "newspaper" shall be deemed to be categorised`
  line `as big, medium or small newspaper on the basis of its circulation per issue, as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, notify from time to time.]`
  line
  line `(4) Before making any nomination under clause (a), clause (b) or clause (c) sub-section (3), the`
  line `Central Government in the case of the first Council and the retiring Chairman of the previous Council in`
  line `the case of any subsequent Council shall, in the prescribed manner, invite panels of names comprising`
  line `twice the number of members to be nominated from such associations of persons of the categories`
  line `referred to in the said clause (a), clause (b) or clause (c) as may be notified in this behalf by the Central`
  line `Government in the case of the first Council and by the Council itself in the case of subsequent Councils:`
  line
  line `Provided that where there is no association of persons of the category referred to in the said`
  line `clause (c), the panels of names shall be invited from such news agencies as may be notified as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government shall notify the names of persons nominated as members under`
  line `sub-section (3) in the Official Gazette and every such nomination shall take effect from the date on which`
  line `it is notified.`
  line
  line `(6) The members of the Council notified under sub-section (5) shall elect from among themselves in`
  line `accordance with such procedure as may be prescribed, a person to be a member of the Committee referred`
  line `to in sub-section (2) and a meeting of the members of the Council for the purpose of such election shall be`
  line `prescribed over by a person chosen from among themselves.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (9078)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Term of office and retirement of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9078&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this section, the`
  line `Chairman and other members shall hold office for a period of three years:`
  line `Provided that the Chairman shall continue to hold such office until the Council is reconstituted in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of section 5 or for a period of six months whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a person nominated as a member under clause (a), clause (b) or clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 5 is censured under the provisions of sub-section (1) of section 14, he shall`
  line `cease to be a member of the Council.`
  line
  line `(3) The term of office of a member nominated under clause (e) of sub-section (3) of section 5 shall`
  line `come to an end as soon as he ceases to be a member of the House from which he was nominated.`
  line
  line `(4) A member shall be deemed to have vacated his seat if he is absent without excuse, sufficient in the`
  line `opinion of the Council, from three consecutive meetings of the Council.`
  line
  line `(5) The Chairman may resign his office by giving notice in writing to the Central Government, and`
  line `any other member may resign his office by giving notice in writing to the Chairman, and upon such`
  line `resignation being accepted by the Central Government, or as the case may be, the Chairman or the`
  line `member shall be deemed to have vacated his office.`
  line
  line `(6) Any vacancy arising under sub-section (2), sub-section (3), sub-section (4) or sub-section (5) or`
  line `otherwise shall be filled, as soon as may be, by nomination in the same manner in which the member`
  line `vacating office was nominated and the member so nominated shall hold office for the remaining period in`
  line `which the member in whose place he is nominated would have held office.`
  line
  line `(7) A retiring member shall be eligible for re-nomination for not more than one term.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (9079)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Conditions of service of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9079&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairman shall be a whole-time officer and shall be`
  line `paid such salary as the Central Government may think fit; and the other members shall receive such`
  line `allowances of fees for attending the meetings of the Council, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1), the conditions of service of members shall be such as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) It is hereby declared that the office of a member of the Council shall not disqualify its holder for`
  line `being chosen as, or for being, a member of either House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (9080)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Committees of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9080&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of performing its functions under this Act, the`
  line `Council may constitute from among its members such Committees for general or special purposes as it`
  line `may deem necessary and every Committee so constituted shall perform such functions as are assigned to`
  line `it by the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall have the power to co-opt as members of any committee constituted under`
  line `sub-section (1) such other number of persons, not being members of the Council, as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(3) Any such member shall have the right to attend any meeting of the Committee on which he is so`
  line `co-opted and to take part in the discussions thereat, but shall not have the right to vote and shall not be a`
  line `member for any other purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (9081)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Meetings of the Council and committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9081&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The Council or any committee thereof shall meet at`
  line `such times and places and shall observe such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at`
  line `its meetings as may be provided by regulations made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (9082)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Vacancies among members or defect in the constitution not to invalidate acts and proceedings of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9082&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the Council shall be deemed to be invalid by`
  line `reason merely of the existence of any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (9083)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Staff of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9083&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such rules as may be made by the Central Government in`
  line `this behalf, the Council may appoint a Secretary and such other employees as it may think necessary for`
  line `the efficient performance of its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The terms and conditions of service of the employees shall be such as may be determined by`
  line regulations.
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (9084)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Authentication of orders and other instruments of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9084&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `All orders and decisions of`
  line `the Council shall be authenticated by the signature of the Chairman or any other member authorised by`
  line `the Council in this behalf and other instruments issued by the Council shall be authenticated by the`
  line `signature of the Secretary or any other officer of the Council authorised in like manner in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (9085)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Objects and functions of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9085&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The objects of the Council shall be to preserve the`
  line `freedom of the Press and to maintain and improve the standards of newspapers and news agencies in`
  line India.
  line
  line `(2) The Council may, in furtherance of its objects, perform the following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to help newspapers and news agencies to maintain their independence;`
  line
  line `(b) to build up a code of conduct for newspapers, news agencies and journalists in accordance`
  line `with high professional standards;`
  line
  line `(c) to ensure on the part of newspapers, news agencies and journalists, the maintenance of high`
  line `standards of public taste and foster a due sense of both the rights and responsibilities of citizenship;`
  line
  line `(d) to encourage the growth of a sense of responsibility and public service among all those`
  line `engaged in the profession of journalism;`
  line
  line `(e) to keep under review any development likely to restrict the supply and dissemination of news`
  line `of public interest and importance;`
  line
  line `(f) to keep under review cases of assistance received by any newspaper or news agency in India`
  line `from any foreign source including such cases as are referred to it by the Central Government or are`
  line `brought to its notice by any individual, association of persons or any other organisation:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this clause shall preclude the Central Government from dealing with any`
  line `case of assistance received by a newspaper or news agency in India from any foreign source in any`
  line `other manner it thinks fit;`
  line
  line `(g) to undertake studies of foreign newspapers, including those brought out by any embassy or`
  line `other representatives in India of a foreign State, their circulation and impact.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this clause, the expression "foreign State" has the meaning`
  line `assigned to it in section 87A of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908);`
  line
  line `(h) to promote a proper functional relationship among all classes of persons engaged in the`
  line `production or publication of newspapers or in news agencies:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this clause shall be deemed to confer on the Council any functions in`
  line `regard to disputes to which the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), applies;`
  line
  line `(i) to concern itself developments such as concentration of or other aspects of ownership of`
  line `newspapers and news agencies which may affect the independence of the Press;`
  line
  line `(j) to undertake such studies as may be entrusted to the Council and to express its opinion in`
  line `regard to any matter referred to it by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(k) to do such other acts as may be incidental or conductive to the discharge of the above`
  line functions.
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (9086)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to censure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9086&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, on receipt of a complaint made to it or otherwise, the Council has`
  line `reason to believe that a newspaper or news agency has offended against the standards or journalistic`
  line `ethics or public taste or that an editor or a working journalist has committed any professional misconduct,`
  line `the Council may, after giving the newspaper, or news agency, the editor or journalist concerned an`
  line `opportunity of being heard, hold an inquiry in such manner as may be provided by regulations made`
  line `under this Act and, if it is satisfied that it is necessary so to do, it may, for reasons to be recorded in`
  line `writing, warn, admonish or censure the newspaper, the news agency, the editor or the journalist or`
  line `disapprove the conduct of the editor or the journalist, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Council may not take cognizance of a compliant if in the opinion of the Chairman,`
  line `there is no sufficient ground for holding an inquiry.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Council is of the opinion that it is necessary or expedient in the public interest so to do, it`
  line `may require any newspaper to publish therein in such manner as the Council thinks fit, any particulars`
  line `relating to any inquiry under this section against a newspaper or news agency, an editor or a journalist`
  line `working therein, including the name of such newspaper, news agency, editor or journalist.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to empower the Council to hold an inquiry into any`
  line `matter in respect of which any proceeding is pending in a court of law.`
  line
  line `(4) The decision of the Council under sub-section (1), or sub-section (2), as the case may be, shall be`
  line `final and shall not be questioned in any court of law.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (9087)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `General powers of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9087&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of performing its functions or holding any`
  line `inquiry under this Act, the Council shall have the same powers throughout India as are vested in a civil`
  line `court while trying a suit under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the following`
  line `matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of persons and examining them on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and inspection of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or copies thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents; and`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter, which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to compel any newspaper, news agency, editor or`
  line `journalist to disclose the source of any news or information published by that newspaper or received or`
  line `reported by that news agency, editor or journalist.`
  line
  line `(3) Every inquiry held by the Council shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the meaning`
  line `of sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(4) The Council may, if it considers it necessary for the purpose of carrying out its objects or for the`
  line `performance of any of its functions under this Act, make such observations, as it may think fit, in any of`
  line `its decisions or reports, respecting the conduct of any authority, including Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (9088)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Levy of fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9088&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may, for the purpose of performing its functions under this Act,`
  line `levy such fees, at such rates and in such manner, as may be prescribed, from registered newspapers and`
  line `news agencies and different rates may be prescribed for different newspapers having regard to their`
  line `circulation and other matters.`
  line
  line `(2) Any fees payable to the Council under sub-section (1) may be recovered as an arrear of land`
  line revenue.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (9089)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Payments to the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9089&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due appropriation made by`
  line `Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Council by way of grants such sums of money as the Central`
  line `Government may consider necessary for the performance of the functions of the Council under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (9090)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Fund of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9090&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall have its own fund, and the fees collected by it, all`
  line `such sums as may, from time to time, be paid to it by the Central Government and all grants and advances`
  line `made to it by any other authority or person shall be credited to the Fund and all payments by the Council`
  line `shall be made therefrom.`
  line
  line `(2) All moneys belonging to the Fund shall be deposited in such banks or invested in such manner as`
  line `may, subject to the approval of the Central Government, be decided by the Council.`
  line
  line `(3) The Council may spend such sums as it thinks fit for performing its functions under this Act, and`
  line `such sums shall be treated as expenditure payable out of the Fund of the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (9091)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9091&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Council shall prepare, in such form and at such time each year as may be`
  line `prescribed, a budget in respect of the financial year next ensuing showing the estimated receipts and`
  line `expenditure, and copies thereof shall be forwarded to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (9092)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9092&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The Council shall prepare once every year, in such form and at such time as`
  line `may be prescribed, an annual report, giving a summary of its activities during the previous year, and`
  line `giving an account of the standards of newspapers and news agencies and factors affecting them, and`
  line `copies thereof, together with the statement of accounts audited in the manner prescribed under section 22`
  line `shall be forwarded to the Central Government and the Government shall cause the same to be laid before`
  line `both Houses of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (9093)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Interim reports.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9093&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to the provisions of section 20, the Council may prepare at`
  line `any time during the course of a year, a report giving a summary of such of its activities during the year as`
  line `it considers to be of public importance and copies thereof shall be forwarded to the Central Government`
  line `and the Government shall cause the same to be laid before both Houses of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (9094)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9094&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The accounts of the Council shall be maintained and audited in such`
  line `manner as may, in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India, be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (9095)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9095&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against`
  line `the Council or any member thereof or any person acting under the direction of the Council in respect of`
  line `anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against any newspaper in respect of the publication of`
  line `any matter therein under the authority of the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (9096)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Members, etc., to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9096&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Every member of the Council and every officer or other`
  line `employee appointed by the Council shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of`
  line `section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (9097)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9097&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that when the Council has been established, no such rules shall be made without consulting`
  line `the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the procedure for nomination of members of the Council under clauses (a), (b) and (c) of`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which panels of names may be invited under sub-section (4) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(c) the procedure for election of a member of the Committee referred to in sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 5 under sub-section (6) of that section;`
  line
  line `(d) the allowances of fees to be paid to the members of the Council for attending the meetings of`
  line `the Council, and other conditions of service of such members under sub-section (1) and (2) of`
  line `section 7;`
  line
  line `(e) the appointment of the Secretary and other employees of the Council under section 11;`
  line
  line `(f) the matters referred to in clause (f) of sub-section (1) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(g) the rates at which fees may be levied by the Council under section 16 and the manner in`
  line `which such fees may be levied;`
  line
  line `(h) the form in which, and the time within which, the budget and annual report are to be prepared`
  line `by the Council under sections 19 and 20 respectively;`
  line
  line `(i) the manner in which the accounts of the Council are to be maintained and audited under`
  line `section 22.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (9098)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9098&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] The Council may ^2[by notification in the Official Gazette]`
  line `make regulations not inconsistent with this Act thereof and the rules made thereunder, for--`
  line
  line `(a) regulating the meetings of the Council or any committee thereof and the procedure for`
  line `conducting the business thereat under section 9;`
  line
  line `(b) specifying the terms and conditions of service of the employees, appointed by the Council,`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(c) regulating the manner of holding any inquiry under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) delegating to the Chairman or the Secretary of the Council, subject to such conditions as it`
  line `may think fit to impose, any of its powers under sub-section (3) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter for which provision may be made by regulations under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the regulations made under clause (b) shall be made only with the prior approval of the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The Central Government shall cause every regulation made under this Act to be laid, as soon as`
  line `may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty`
  line `days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the`
  line `expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses`
  line `agree in making any modification in the regulation or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be`
  line `made, the regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case`
  line `may be; so, however, that any modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that regulation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 26 re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-3-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 2 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-3-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (9099)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Amendment of Act 25 of 1867.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006&sectionId=9099&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00008_197837_1517807325006
